<p>

<b>Subscribing to the <tt>ciao-users</tt> mailing list:</b> If you
download any Ciao-related software, we highly recommended that you
subscribe to the <a
href=mailto:ciao-users@clip.dia.fi.upm.es><tt>ciao-users@clip.dia.fi.upm.es</tt></a>
mailing list, so that you receive updates, bug fixes, and any other
related info.  You can subscribe by checking the approriate
option during the download process, or by sending an ascii message to <a
href=mailto:ciao-users-request@clip.dia.fi.upm.es><tt>ciao-users-request@clip.dia.fi.upm.es</tt></a>,
containing in the body the word <b>subscribe</b> alone in one
line. Discussion is limited to Ciao-Prolog related topics and we will
keep your email address strictly confidential.  An <a
href=http://www.clip.dia.fi.upm.es/Mail/ciao-users/>archive of all
messages to the list</a> is available.

<p>

<b>Version note:</b> Not all versions of the Ciao system components
are guaranteed to work together. On the other hand the <em>current
versions</em> in this page have typically been checked to be fully
compatible. Thus, if you download one component and also use other
components, we recommend downloading the newer version of those
components too.

